<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="6" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,266,1947]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,318,1755,1781]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Zaitzev" authorityName="Zaitzev" box="[682,976,1755,1781]" class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Hemipenthes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mesasiatica">
<emphasis box="[682,857,1755,1780]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">H. mesasiatica</emphasis>
(Zaitzev)
</taxonomicName>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the hyaline part of cell 
<emphasis box="[475,527,1795,1820]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">cu-a</emphasis>
<emphasis box="[526,534,1811,1825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<number box="[526,534,1811,1825]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="1.0">1</number>
</emphasis>
smaller, the epiphallus distinctly narrowing at middle, and the distiphallus subquadrate in dorsal view. In 
<emphasis box="[518,700,1838,1863]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
